Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrazakthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazak Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/29/02 4:44:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2412.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Credit</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
i naively wish that those who have the &quot;because i CAN, i DESERVE to, and i WILL&quot; attitude would read your post and take some of it to heart.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, while I'd love to take credit for this type of thinking, but I can't. I am of a firm belief that if the game allows you to do something, and you want to do it, you should. You pay for it, and I pay for it. Do it if you want. <br>
<br>
That's probably oversimplified, and personal beliefs are a huge part of the equation. <br>
<br>
Unfortunately, the blame here, IMO, really falls on Verant. I think Waking the Sleeper is just a very poorly designed and implemented event. But, I understand the logic behind it - they wanted to see how it would work. We Beta-tested it for them. Now they know. I hope they've learned from the experience. <br>
<br>
Some things in EQ aren't &quot;fair&quot;, IMO. Waking the Sleeper, as I wrote above, IMO, removes equal opportunity for everyone. I think that's unfair. But who's to really blame for that? The players, or Verant, or both? <br>
<br>
I think people like to blame the players a lot, and IMO, the bulk of the blame lies with Verant for designing and implementing the encounter in the first place. <br>
<br>
Now, we could get into a HUGE debate about &quot;should people DO a certain thing if they CAN?&quot;. Well, that's more than I want to deal with. <br>
<br>
Basically, I think that Waking the Sleeper is a bad idea. It removes an experience in the game that everyone could partake in. It takes away some loot that everyone has acccess to UNTIL this event happens. I think it's a bad idea. <br>
<br>
But, if a group of players decides to do it, I'm not going to stand here and soapbox about what bad people they are. I mean, the game has that scripted event in there just so they can do it. It's like putting a big red button in the Bond car... you just KNOW if you were sitting in that thing that it would be hard not to press it... Some people can resist that urge, others can't. <br>
<br>
It's not my business to judge players who choose Wake the Sleeper. But it is my business, as a player, to judge Verant, and their game. <br>
<br>
In this instance, I think their beta-testing resulted in a bad idea that affects a lot of players. <br>
<br>
Personally - I wish they'd just encourage all guilds to Wake the Sleeper, and then reset that zone so that killing all 4 warders does NOT result in another wakening... <br>
<br>
<br>
But maybe that's what this revamp on Stormhammer is suppose to be. <br>
<br>
-Krazak<br>
